6446 /******************************************************************************/
6447 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
6448 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
6449 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
6450 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
6451 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
6452 /******************************************************************************/
6453 
6454 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
6455 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
6456 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
6457 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
6458 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
6459 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
6460 #define RCC_CRS_IRQn RCC_IRQn
6461 
6462 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
6463 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
6464 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
6465 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
6466 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
6467 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
6468 #define RCC_CRS_IRQHandler RCC_IRQHandler
6469 
6470 #ifdef __cplusplus
6471 }
6472 #endif /* __cplusplus */
6473 
6474 #endif /* __STM32F030x6_H */
